						<div class="postbody">Sorry for the late reply. I have now tested it on both my PAL and my NTSC NES. They both give the same results: 57600 works fine while 115200 fails completely. <br /><br />I am a bit curious as to why of course. Since other people haven't reported any such problems with the Dealextreme cable, it could just be my computr or Ubuntu limiting it in some weird way. Or slightly more far-fetched: maybe the length of the cable actually starts to matter at this higher speed? <br /><br />When I get some visitor with a different computer I could try the first two theories, and since I bought two cables I have yet another one for testing the second theory when I'm bored enough to do some more soldering...</div>

